---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../styles/global.css";

---

<Layout
  title="wrangle vs Obsidian — markdown editor for AI development workflows"
  description="Obsidian is a personal knowledge base. wrangle is a native macOS markdown editor purpose-built for AI agent workflows — embedded terminals, token counting, and CLAUDE.md awareness."
  canonical="https://wrangleapp.dev/compare/obsidian"
>
  <!-- Header -->
  <header class="flex items-center justify-between px-5 lg:px-[200px] py-4">
    <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-2.5">
      <img
        src="/images/wrangle-logo-13.png"
        alt="wrangle logo"
        class="w-8 h-8 rounded"
      />
      <span class="text-base font-bold">wrangle</span>
    </a>
    <a
      href="https://github.com/J-Krush/wrangle/releases/latest"
      class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-linear-to-b from-teal to-teal-dark px-6 py-2.5 text-sm font-bold text-dark hover:brightness-110 transition-all"
    >
      Download for macOS
    </a>
  </header>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="flex flex-col items-center px-5 lg:px-[200px] pt-16 lg:pt-[100px] pb-12 lg:pb-[80px] gap-8">
    <h1 class="text-[28px] sm:text-[36px] lg:text-[48px] font-bold text-center leading-[1.15] max-w-[1040px]">
      wrangle vs Obsidian
    </h1>
    <p class="text-secondary text-base lg:text-lg text-center leading-relaxed max-w-[800px]">
      Obsidian is a brilliant tool for building a personal knowledge base. but if you're editing AI config files and running agent sessions, you need something with a different focus entirely.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- The Problem -->
  <section class="flex flex-col items-center px-5 lg:px-[200px] py-16 lg:py-[100px] gap-8">
    <div class="w-full max-w-[1040px] flex flex-col gap-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">// different tools, different jobs</h2>
      <p class="text-secondary text-base leading-relaxed max-w-[700px]">
        Obsidian is built around vaults, backlinks, and graph views. it's designed for note-taking, journaling, and connecting ideas. that's a great product — but it's not what you need when you're iterating on a CLAUDE.md file while three agents run in parallel.
      </p>
      <p class="text-secondary text-base leading-relaxed max-w-[700px]">
        wrangle doesn't have backlinks or a graph view. it has embedded terminals, agent notifications, and token counting. it's the workspace for the actual work of AI-native development.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Comparison -->
  <section class="flex flex-col items-center px-5 lg:px-[200px] py-16 lg:py-[100px] gap-8">
    <div class="w-full max-w-[1040px] flex flex-col gap-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">// where wrangle wins</h2>
      <div class="h-2"></div>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-5">
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-teal-dark text-base">→</span>
          <span class="text-base font-bold">embedded terminals</span>
          <span class="text-tertiary text-base hidden sm:inline">—</span>
          <span class="text-secondary text-base">run claude code, gemini, or any CLI agent in tabbed terminals inside the app. Obsidian has no terminal at all.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-teal-dark text-base">→</span>
          <span class="text-base font-bold">agent notifications</span>
          <span class="text-tertiary text-base hidden sm:inline">—</span>
          <span class="text-secondary text-base">native macOS notifications when an agent needs input, finishes, or requests permission. context-switch away without worry.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-teal-dark text-base">→</span>
          <span class="text-base font-bold">token counting</span>
          <span class="text-tertiary text-base hidden sm:inline">—</span>
          <span class="text-secondary text-base">always in the status bar. when you're crafting prompts, knowing your token count is essential — not a nice-to-have.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-teal-dark text-base">→</span>
          <span class="text-base font-bold">xml-in-markdown</span>
          <span class="text-tertiary text-base hidden sm:inline">—</span>
          <span class="text-secondary text-base">&lt;tools&gt;, &lt;instructions&gt;, &lt;system&gt; blocks get proper highlighting and collapsing. Obsidian treats these as raw HTML.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-teal-dark text-base">→</span>
          <span class="text-base font-bold">AI file awareness</span>
          <span class="text-tertiary text-base hidden sm:inline">—</span>
          <span class="text-secondary text-base">CLAUDE.md, SKILL.md, AGENTS.md are first-class citizens with distinct icons and behavior. not just another .md file in a vault.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-teal-dark text-base">→</span>
          <span class="text-base font-bold">native macOS</span>
          <span class="text-tertiary text-base hidden sm:inline">—</span>
          <span class="text-secondary text-base">swift and swiftUI on apple silicon. Obsidian is electron. you feel the difference in responsiveness and memory usage.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-teal-dark text-base">→</span>
          <span class="text-base font-bold">session context</span>
          <span class="text-tertiary text-base hidden sm:inline">—</span>
          <span class="text-secondary text-base">see which CLAUDE.md file, skills, and MCP servers are linked to each running agent session.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Where Obsidian Wins -->
  <section class="flex flex-col items-center px-5 lg:px-[200px] py-16 lg:py-[100px] gap-8">
    <div class="w-full max-w-[1040px] flex flex-col gap-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">// where Obsidian wins</h2>
      <p class="text-secondary text-base leading-relaxed max-w-[700px]">
        Obsidian is unmatched for personal knowledge management. backlinks, graph view, daily notes, templates, and a massive plugin ecosystem make it the best tool for building a second brain. if you're organizing research, taking meeting notes, or building a personal wiki, Obsidian is the right call.
      </p>
      <p class="text-secondary text-base leading-relaxed max-w-[700px]">
        it also runs on every platform — Windows, Linux, macOS, iOS, Android. wrangle is macOS-only.
      </p>
      <p class="text-secondary text-base leading-relaxed max-w-[700px]">
        these tools aren't really competing. use Obsidian for your knowledge base. use wrangle for your AI development workspace. they solve different problems.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who Should Switch -->
  <section class="flex flex-col items-center px-5 lg:px-[200px] py-16 lg:py-[100px] gap-8">
    <div class="w-full max-w-[1040px] flex flex-col gap-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">// you might want wrangle if</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-teal-dark text-base">→</span>
          <span class="text-secondary text-base">you've been using Obsidian to edit CLAUDE.md files and it feels like the wrong tool</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-teal-dark text-base">→</span>
          <span class="text-secondary text-base">you want to run AI agents and edit their config files in the same app</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-teal-dark text-base">→</span>
          <span class="text-secondary text-base">you need token counting for prompt engineering, not backlinks for note-taking</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-teal-dark text-base">→</span>
          <span class="text-secondary text-base">you don't need vaults, graph view, or plugins — you need terminals and notifications</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quick Comparison Table -->
  <section class="flex flex-col items-center px-5 lg:px-[200px] py-16 lg:py-[100px] gap-8">
    <div class="w-full max-w-[1040px] flex flex-col gap-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">// quick comparison</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <th class="text-left py-3 pr-4 text-tertiary font-medium"></th>
              <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-teal-dark font-bold">wrangle</th>
              <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 font-bold">Obsidian</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="text-secondary">
            <tr class="border-b border-border-subtle">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-primary">focus</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">AI development workspace</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">personal knowledge base</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border-subtle">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-primary">embedded terminals</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">yes, tabbed</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">no</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border-subtle">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-primary">agent notifications</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">native macOS alerts</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">no</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border-subtle">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-primary">token counting</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">built-in, always visible</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">plugin required</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border-subtle">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-primary">XML in markdown</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">highlighted + collapsible</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">rendered as HTML</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border-subtle">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-primary">backlinks / graph</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">no</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">yes, excellent</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border-subtle">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-primary">runtime</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">native macOS (Swift)</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Electron</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border-subtle">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-primary">platforms</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">macOS only</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">everywhere</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-primary">price</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">free + open source</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">free (sync is $8/mo)</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center px-5 lg:px-[200px] py-16 lg:py-[100px] gap-6">
    <h2 class="text-[32px] lg:text-[40px] font-bold">wrangle</h2>
    <p class="text-secondary text-base text-center max-w-[500px]">
      the markdown editor built for AI agent workflows. not note-taking — agent wrangling. free + open source.
    </p>
    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center gap-3">
      <a
        href="https://github.com/J-Krush/wrangle/releases/latest"
        class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-linear-to-b from-teal to-teal-dark px-8 py-4 text-base font-bold text-dark hover:brightness-110 transition-all"
      >
        Download for macOS
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/J-Krush/wrangle"
        class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-lg border border-border px-8 py-4 text-base font-bold text-primary hover:border-teal-dark hover:text-teal transition-all"
      >
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M8 0C3.58 0 0 3.58 0 8c0 3.54 2.29 6.53 5.47 7.59.4.07.55-.17.55-.38 0-.19-.01-.82-.01-1.49-2 .37-2.53-.49-2.69-.94-.09-.23-.48-.94-.82-1.13-.28-.15-.68-.52-.01-.53.63-.01 1.08.58 1.23.82.72 1.21 1.87.87 2.33.66.07-.52.28-.87.51-1.07-1.78-.2-3.64-.89-3.64-3.95 0-.87.31-1.59.82-2.15-.08-.2-.36-1.02.08-2.12 0 0 .67-.21 2.2.82.64-.18 1.32-.27 2-.27.68 0 1.36.09 2 .27 1.53-1.04 2.2-.82 2.2-.82.44 1.1.16 1.92.08 2.12.51.56.82 1.27.82 2.15 0 3.07-1.87 3.75-3.65 3.95.29.25.54.73.54 1.48 0 1.07-.01 1.93-.01 2.2 0 .21.15.46.55.38A8.013 8.013 0 0 0 16 8c0-4.42-3.58-8-8-8z"/></svg>
        Star on GitHub
      </a>
    </div>
    <span class="text-tertiary text-sm">macOS 15+ · apple silicon · free + open source</span>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer class="flex items-center justify-between px-5 lg:px-[200px] py-5 border-t border-border-subtle">
    <div class="flex gap-3 text-tertiary text-sm">
      <span>© 2026 wrangle</span>
      <span>·</span>
      <a href="https://jkrush.dev" target="_blank" class="hover:text-secondary transition-colors">Built by J Krush</a>
      <span>·</span>
      <a href="./LICENSE" class="hover:text-secondary transition-colors">MIT</a>
    </div>
    <div class="flex gap-3 text-tertiary text-sm">
      <a href="mailto:support@wrangleapp.dev" class="hover:text-secondary transition-colors">support</a>
      <span>·</span>
      <a href="https://github.com/J-Krush/wrangle" class="hover:text-secondary transition-colors">github</a>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Layout>
